widgets_values:
length is crucial parameter.
time in WAN goes with 16 frames per seconds speed
you can create video up to 81 frames (5 seconds), but each additional second will increase total time radicaly

example:
without speedups it will take (4090)
~24 seconds per step on 77 frames (>8 minutes for 20 steps)
~20 seconds per step on 61 frames (6:30 for 20 steps)
~9 seconds per step on 37 frames (3 minutes for 20 steps)
~4 seconds per frame for 17 frames (1:20 for 20 steps)

for 480p model up to 0.39

on 24gb vram)
0.39  for up to 77 frames
0.38  for 81 frames 

this gives 480p videos, or 640x640 square
but for 24gb vram you can do only up to 77 frames
otherwise resolution should be decreased

same as shift parameter in flux
could be left at default value

will add some time to prepare this node during the first run
if you change resolution or frame count it will be recalculated again
20% speedup from base speed
with tolerable quality penalty

put to auto to enable
put to disable to disable

instant 25% speedup from base speed
severe quality penalty

TeaCache:
40% speedup from base speed
huge penalty for movement and blurness, only usable for low motion scene

But you can increase amount of steps

The Skip Guidance node is for quality compensation
